news.title: Asian Paints' net profit dips 4.83% in Q3 FY26
news.para: Asian Paints announced its financial results for the quarter ending December 31, 2025. The company's net consolidated profit saw a decrease of 4.83 percent. Despite this, total income grew by 3.86 percent.

news.title: WeWork India posts net profit of ₹16.78 crore in Q3 FY26
news.para: WeWork India  reported a net profit of over ₹16 crore for the quarter ending December 31, 2025. This marks a turnaround from a loss in the same period last year. Total income also saw a substantial rise.

news.title: Raymond Realty posts net profit of ₹66.79 crore in Q3 FY26
news.para: Raymond Realty's profit after tax surged to ₹66.79 crore in the quarter ending December 31, 2025. This marks an increase from ₹3.01 crore in the same period last year. The company's total income also saw a jump to ₹765.97 crore.

news.title: India's luxury housing market may cool down in FY27, feel 56% of HNIs in ISIR survey
news.para: Luxury home demand and prices might decrease in India's major cities next fiscal year. A survey of wealthy individuals shows over half expect a market moderation. Despite this, most remain optimistic about India's economic growth.

news.title: Delhi government working towards improving living standards of slum residents: CM
news.para: Delhi Chief Minister Rekha Gupta celebrated Republic Day with slum dwellers,  inaugurating development projects valued at Rs 327 crore. The government has allocated Rs 144 crore for various projects, aiming to enhance living standards and provide essential amenities for residents.

news.title: Lorazzo raises ₹5 crore in seed funding led by Sprout Venture Partners, India Quotient
news.para: Home improvement startup Lorazzo secured ₹5 crore in seed funding. The investment, led by Sprout Venture Partners and India Quotient, will boost product development and expand distribution.

news.title: Pune stamp duty collections cross ₹7,100 crore in 2025: Knight Frank
news.para: Pune's property landscape reached a milestone in 2025, recording an exceptional stamp duty revenue of over ₹7,100 crore. Despite a slight reduction in property registrations, the surge in sales of higher-value homes drove growth in revenue. There is a strong demand for larger, premium properties among buyers.

news.title: Housing sales dips 14% in top seven cities: Report
news.para: In 2025, the housing market saw a significant decline in sales volume, yet the total value of property transactions soared. This suggests a transformative shift in buyer preferences, with an increasing appetite for upscale residences and more spacious living options.

news.title: Barricades at Noida sector 150 plot with ‘illegal ads’ removed in 2021
news.para: A commercial plot owner, Wiztown Planners, claims Noida Authority ordered the removal of barricades in July 2021, which were later found to be a factor in a software engineer's drowning. Wiztown's director was arrested, and the company alleges the Authority's sewer lines caused sewage to flood the plot. The Authority denies compromising safety, stating only advertisements on barricades were removed.

news.title: Gurugram: License of commercial project lapsed, developer served notice by DTCP
news.para: The Directorate of Town and Country Planning (DTCP) has issued a regulatory notice to a developer for non-compliance on a commercial colony project in Sector 65. Licenses granted in 2011-2012 expired without renewal, and the developer failed to transfer master plan road land to the government. Authorities have given 30 days to rectify deficiencies.

news.title: About 13 builders fined for water extraction, but Noida authority says they bought it
news.para: Conflicting statements from Uttar Pradesh Pollution Control Board and Noida Authority have surfaced before the National Green Tribunal. The issue concerns builders allegedly extracting groundwater illegally in Greater Noida. While one authority suggests penalties, the other claims some builders purchased treated water. The tribunal is set to hear the matter soon.

news.title: What real estate stakeholders expect from Budget 2026
news.para: Real estate leaders are urging the government for key policy changes in the Union Budget 2026. They want measures to boost housing affordability and liquidity.  Suggestions include reviving buyer incentives, easing GST, and increasing institutional capital.  The sector aims to address rising costs and buyer preferences for sustained economic expansion.

news.title: CEPT University's new MBA in real estate program targets talent gaps in industry
news.para: CEPT University introduces a new MBA in real estate. This program aims to equip professionals with skills across design, planning, construction, finance, and management. The curriculum is developed with industry input to address the sector's growing corporatization and formalization.

news.title: Lucknow civic body to bring proposal to hike licence fee for hotels, commercial units
news.para: The Lucknow Municipal Corporation is set to propose a significant hike in licence fees for hotels, restaurants, nursing homes, and commercial units, with increases potentially reaching five times the current rates. This revision, aimed at enhancing revenue and ensuring compliance, will be presented for approval on January 27 and is slated for enforcement from April 1, 2026.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh CM pushes bill for Amaravati capital status in parliament
news.para: Andhra Pradesh Chief Minister Chandrababu Naidu announced plans to introduce a Bill in Parliament to grant legal status to Amaravati as the state capital. He urged MPs to secure central funds for development projects, including the Polavaram and Purvodaya initiatives, and to safeguard the state's interests during the budget session.

news.title: MDDA clears 10,000 bighas of encroached land in Dehradun in three years
news.para: The Mussoorie Dehradun Development Authority (MDDA) has conducted a rigorous anti-encroachment drive, clearing over 10,000 bigha of land and sealing more than 1,000 illegal constructions in the past three years. This decisive campaign aims to curb unauthorized plotting and construction, ensuring planned development and public safety across Dehradun.

news.title: UP-RERA facilitates ₹2,040 crore relief for homebuyers, resolves over 11,300 cases in 2025
news.para: The Uttar Pradesh Real Estate Regulatory Authority has successfully secured ₹2,040 crore by addressing over 11,300 protracted disputes. Utilizing a blend of recovery tactics, friendly negotiations, and conflict-resolution techniques, the authority tackled numerous cases primarily focusing on delayed possession and refund issues.

news.title: Telangana to conduct forensic audit of land transactions in all districts
news.para: Following a pilot audit revealing violations in Siddipet and Sircilla, the Telangana government will conduct forensic audits across all districts to uncover Dharani portal irregularities. The audit, assisted by a central government-affiliated agency, found serious issues during the previous BRS government's tenure, leading to criminal cases against 48 individuals for unpaid government dues and land grabbing.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh: 60-40 registration model cuts costs for MIG plot buyers
news.para: Andhra Pradesh government has introduced a 60-40 model for MIG plot registrations under the Dr NTR Smart Township scheme, significantly reducing costs for thousands. This split, treating 60% as sale price and 40% as development charges, lowers registration fees, saving buyers substantial amounts. The initiative aims to provide affordable housing sites for middle-income groups across the state.

news.title: HC rejects YEIDA’s appeal to review its township land order
news.para: Allahabad High Court dismissed review petitions by Yamuna Expressway Industrial Development Authority (YEIDA), refusing to revisit its order for land handover to Silverline Furnishing. The court found no apparent error in its previous judgment, stating YEIDA failed to provide physical possession of promised land for a residential township project.
